This paper analyzes the diversity of software versions in Maven Central, which is a software repository. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with versioning and dependency management, which are topics related to programming languages, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely category. The paper also uses data analysis techniques to draw conclusions, which could place it in the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with software artifacts, which could place it in the category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
